  • Method Details

    • getType

      String getType()
      Returns the value of the 'Type' attribute. Fully qualified class name. Mutually exclusive with ``service`` and ``property``. One of ``class``, ``property``, or ``service`` is required. For SupplierFactory adapter, if the class implements SupplierFactory then it is instantiated and then its ``create()`` method is invoked to create a supplier. If the class implements Supplier, then it is instantiated. If there are no ``init`` arguments, then the supplier is diagnosed as part of ``diagnose()``. Otherwise it is diagnosed in ``execute()`` and diagnostic results are discarded. Similar processing will be implemented for Consumer and Command.
      Returns:
      the value of the 'Type' attribute.
      See Also:
      • setType(String)
      • ExecPackage.getCall_Type()

    • getMethod

      String getMethod()
      Returns the value of the 'Method' attribute. An optional method to call. In the ``class`` case the method can be static. If the method is static the class is not instantiated and if ``init`` or ``properties`` are present it results in an exception.
      Returns:
      the value of the 'Method' attribute.

    • getProperties

      org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EMap<String,org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> getProperties()
      Returns the value of the 'Properties' map. The key is of type String, and the value is of type EObject, A map injected into the instance in the ``class`` case if the instance implements ${javadoc/java.util.function.BiConsumer} or in the service or property case if they implement SupplierFactory. If elements implement SupplierFactory then the supplier factory is used to produce value to be injected. Otherwise elements are injected AS-IS.
      Returns:
      the value of the 'Properties' map.
      See Also:
      • ExecPackage.getCall_Properties()

    • getInit

      org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> getInit()
      Returns the value of the 'Init' containment reference list. The list contents are of type EObject. An optional array of constructor arguments for the ``class``. Not applicable for ``property`` and ``service``. If elements implement SupplierFactory then the factory is used to produce argument values. Then arguments get converted to constructor parameter types if conversion is available. If conversion is not available, an exception is thrown.
      Returns:
      the value of the 'Init' containment reference list.
      See Also:
      • ExecPackage.getCall_Init()

    • getArguments

      org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> getArguments()
      Returns the value of the 'Arguments' containment reference list. The list contents are of type EObject. An optional array of method arguments. If elements implement SupplierFactory, then the factory is used to produce argument value. Then arguments get converted to method parameter types if conversion is available. If conversion is not available, an exception is thrown.
      Returns:
      the value of the 'Arguments' containment reference list.
      See Also:
      • ExecPackage.getCall_Arguments()
